0" ind2="0" tag="245"><subfield code="a">Critical perspectives on counter-terrorism /</subfield><subfield code="c">edited by Lee Jarvis and Michael Lister.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="1" tag="264"><subfield code="a">Abingdon, Oxon ;</subfield><subfield code="a">New York, NY :</subfield><subfield code="b">Routledge, Taylor &amp; Francis Group,</subfield><subfield code="c">2015.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="300"><subfield code="a">xv, 233 pages ;</subfield><subfield code="c">24 cm.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="336"><subfield code="a">text</subfield><subfield code="2">rdacontent</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="337"><subfield code="a">unmediated</subfield><subfield code="2">rdamedia</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="338"><subfield code="a">volume</subfield><subfield code="2">rdacarrier</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1="1" ind2=" " tag="490"><subfield code="a">Routledge critical terrorism studies</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="504"><subfield code="a">Includes bibliographical references and index.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="520"><subfield code="a">"This volume examines the rationale, effectiveness and consequences of counter terrorism practices from a range of perspectives and cases. The book critically interrogates contemporary counter-terrorism powers from military campaigns and repression through to the prosecution of terrorist suspects, counter-terrorism policing, counter-radicalisation programmes, and the proscription of terrorist organisations. Drawing on a range of timely and important case studies from around the world including the UK, Sri Lanka, Spain, Canada, Australia and the USA, its chapters explore the impacts of counter-terrorism on individuals, communities, and political processes. The book focuses on three questions of vital importance to any assessment of counter-terrorism. First, what do counter-terrorism strategies seek to achieve? Second, what are the consequences of different counter-terrorism campaigns, and how are these measured? And, third, how and why do changes to counter-terrorism occur? This volume will be of much interest to students of counter-terrorism, critical terrorism studies, criminology, security studies and IR in general"--</subfield><subfield code="c">Provided by publisher.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="596"><subfield code="a">16 43</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="650"><subfield code="a">Terrorism</subfield><subfield code="x">Prevention.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="650"><subfield code="a">Terrorism</subfield><subfield code="x">Prevention</subfield><subfield code="x">Government policy.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1="1" ind2=" " tag="700"><subfield code="a">Jarvis, Lee,</subfield><subfield code="d">1979-</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1="1" ind2=" " tag="700"><subfield code="a">Lister, Michael,</subfield><subfield code="d">1976-</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="830"><subfield code="a">Critical terrorism studies.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1="4" ind2="2" tag="856"><subfield code="3">Cover image</subfield><subfield code="u">http://images.tandf.co.uk/common/jackets/websmall/978041585/9780415855471.jpg</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="949"><subfield code="a">HV 6431 C7626 2015</subfield><subfield code="c">1</subfield><subfield code="h">UAHS-B</subfield><subfield code="i">0162035229416</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="926"><subfield code="a">HV 6431 C7626 2015</subfield><subfield code="w">LC</subfield><subfield code="c">1</subfield><subfield code="i">0162035229416</subfield><subfield code="d">1/25/2016</subfield><subfield code="e">1/7/2016</subfield><subfield code="l">ON_SHELF</subfield><subfield code="m">UAHSS</subfield><subfield code="n">5</subfield><subfi